identificationModule.briefTitle: Post Market Surveillance Study of the Wingspan Stent System
identificationModule.officialTitle: WEAVE™ Trial: Wingspan StEnt System Post MArket SurVEillance Study

descriptionModule.briefSummary: The primary objective of this study is to evaluate the rate of stroke and/or death in patients treated with the Wingspan Stent System, according to the Indications for Use, within 72 hours post procedure.
descriptionModule.detailedDescription: This research study is a Food and Drug Administration (FDA) mandated post market surveillance study of the Wingspan® Stent System, also known as the WEAVE™ Trial. The purpose of this trial is to fulfill a FDA requirement to evaluate the rate of stroke and/or death within 72 hours of the procedure, in patients who have a Wingspan Stent implanted in accordance with the Indications for Use.

interventions.name: Wingspan Stent System
interventions.description: The Wingspan Stent System is used with the Gateway PTA Balloon Catheter. The Wingspan Stent System is a self-expanding, Nitinol stent and delivery system intended for use in the treatment of intracranial atherosclerotic disease. The Gateway PTA Balloon Catheter is an over-the-wire balloon catheter intended for the pre-dilation of the lesion prior to insertion and deployment of the Wingspan Stent System.

primaryOutcomes.measure: Rate of Stroke or Death Among Participants
primaryOutcomes.description: The primary endpoint in this study is the rate of stroke (ischemic or hemorrhagic) or death within 72 hours of the procedure. Ischemic stroke was defined as a neurological deficit that is thought to have an ischemic cause and is detectable on examination at least 24 hours after onset of symptoms. Hemorrhagic stroke was defined as a symptomatic intracerebral, subarachnoid, or primary intraventricular hemorrhage. The type of stroke was confirmed by imaging.

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Rate of Ischemic Stroke Among Participants
secondaryOutcomes.description: Ischemic stroke was defined as a neurological deficit that is thought to have an ischemic etiology and is detectable on examination at least 24 hours after onset of symptoms.

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Rate of Neurological Death Among Participants
secondaryOutcomes.description: A diagnosis of death by neurological criteria

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Rate of Stroke Recovery Among Participants
secondaryOutcomes.description: Stroke recovery at 90 days post procedure is defined by return to baseline mRS at Day 90.

secondaryOutcomes.measure: Rate of Stroke in the Territory of the Stented Artery Among Participants
secondaryOutcomes.description: Stroke in the vascular territory of the stented artery

measures.title: Baseline modified Rankin Scale
measures.description: mRS scale is as follows: 0 - No symptoms. 1 - No significant disability. Able to carry out all usual activities, despite some symptoms. 2 - Slight disability. Able to look after own affairs without assistance, but unable to carry out all previous activities. 3 - Moderate disability. Requires some help, but able to walk unassisted. 4 - Moderately severe disability. Unable to attend to own bodily needs without assistance, and unable to walk unassisted. 5 - Severe disability. Requires constant nursing care and attention, bedridden, incontinent" or similar).

adverseEventsModule.timeFrame: Serious and Other Adverse Events were monitored/assessed for up to 72 hours post-procedure. All-Cause Mortality was monitored/assessed through 90 days post procedure.
adverseEventsModule.description: Only neurological AEs, bleeding/hemorrhagic AEs (including non-neurological events), groin puncture AEs and AEs that resulted in death experienced by the study subject after enrollment were collected.
